Notes: Though 'row_id' is a generic identifier, it can be interpreted as a pseudo-identifier for the subject related to the measurement, fitting best with the 'hasSubjectPseudoIdentifier' property which likely represents identifiers related to the measurement entity.
The 'patient_id' clearly refers to the patient entity associated with the measurement; the path via 'AIDAVA:hasPatient' to 'AIDAVA:Patient' is the most semantically precise mapping.
The 'measurement_code' corresponds to a coded identifier for the measurement; the path 'hasCode' to 'Code' is semantically the best fit to represent coding schemes or value codes.
'measurement_value' represents the quantitative result of the measurement; 'hasQuantity' pointing to a Quantity entity is the semantically correct path to represent numeric values with units.

The unit is an intrinsic attribute of the Quantity entity referenced by 'hasQuantity'; although not a separate path, it is nested within the Quantity resource related to the measurement value and must be included as part of the Quantity representation.
The date of measurement corresponds exactly to 'hasMeasurementDateTime', a property explicitly for date/time values of a measurement instance, making it the best semantic fit.
